      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Tim Cole has been the Foreign & Commonwealth Office (<abbr title="Foreign & Commonwealth Office">FCO</abbr>) Migration Envoy since October 2017.</p>

<p>Tim previously served as Head of the International Organisations Department, Commonwealth Envoy and, from 2012 to 2016, as Her Majesty’s Ambassador to Cuba. He is an Africa specialist, having served as Deputy Head of Mission in Zimbabwe and Mozambique, Head of Pan-Africa Policy Unit and Adviser to the Prime Minister’s G8 Africa Personal Representative.</p>

<p>Before joining the <abbr title="Foreign & Commonwealth Office">FCO</abbr> he was Save the Children’s Programme Director for the Democratic Republic of Congo and ran Christian Aid’s programme in Central Africa.</p>

